  <!-- 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    Schema: Procedural_solid_model_arm  Type: solid_select 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
   -->
    <ext_description linkend="Procedural_solid_model_arm.solid_select">
 	 A <b>solid_select</b> is a select type used to specify the 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_solid_model:arm:Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid.base_solid"/> 
 as the starting point of a shape modification operation.	 
  </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_solid_model_arm  Entity: Modified_solid 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid">
<p> A <b>Modified_solid</b> is a  type of 
 <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>
that specifies an shape modification operation to create a local modification of a 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_solid_model:arm:Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid.base_solid"/>.
</p>
<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_solid_model_arm  Entity: Modified_solid Attribute base_solid
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid.base_solid">
<p> the initial solid before the shape modification operation specified by the instantiated 
 instance of a subtype of this entity.
</p>
 <note> The particular modification operation is defined in detail by the subtypes of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_solid_model:arm:Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid"/>, the supertype is semantically incomplete.
 </note>

</ext_description>


