<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_solid_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_solid_representation_sequence 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_solid_model_arm.Procedural_solid_representation_sequence">
 A <b>Procedural_solid_representation_sequence</b> is a  type of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence"/>
that specifies a sequence of shape modification operations to create a 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_solid_model:arm:Procedural_solid_model_arm.Modified_solid"/>. It is used to represent the construction history of a 
procedural solid model.

<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note>
</ext_description>

<!-- IP1 -->
 <ext_description linkend="Procedural_solid_model_arm.Procedural_solid_representation_sequence.wr:IP1">
 
 The operations in the list of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.elements"/>.
 shall be such that the final result is a solid model.
 </ext_description>



</ext_descriptions>


